        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "know—acknowledge they are our iniquities.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Our transgressions:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the word here signifies sins of a high nature; such as wherein there is much of man’s will against light; rebellious sins. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Are multiplied before thee:",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " q.d. They admit of no excuse; for they are acted before thee, and multiplied against thee, whereby thou art justly provoked to deny us all help. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Our sins testify; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " every sin that is charged upon is like so many witnesses produced to prove the guilt of our consciences; or, as the Hebrew word, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "do answer",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and so some make it an elegant metaphorical allusion to the echo, which, as it returns the voice again, so those judgments they cry out of are but the meritorious repercussion of their sins. They had been cruel to others, neither had they executed judgment and justice, and here they suffer all kind of cruelties and indignities from the Chaldeans, as the true and just representation or echo of their own works: see a personal instance in Adoni-bezek, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Judges 1:6,7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 1:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ",7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Our transgressions are with us, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. we lie under the guilt of them, they are a burden to us; God hath not yet forgiven them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "As for our iniquities, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " we know them; we are convinced of them; our guilty consciences must own and acknowledge them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Psalm 2 3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It notes either their conviction or sorrow, or both. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 14:7",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 14:7",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Or, we know what are those sins thou art so angry with us for; and this is favoured by the sequel, where they seem to particularize those sins in the following verses. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
